sentences: Nathan Connolly (born 20 January 1981) is a Northern Irish musician, who is best known as the lead guitarist and backing vocalist for alternative rock band Snow Patrol.
With Connolly as a composer of the band's new material, Snow Patrol garnered a new record deal and released Final Straw in 2003.
In late 2006, he talked about plans to record a solo album, which he said would be "melodic and tuneful".
In 2013, Connolly formed his own side project called Little Matador.

After a particularly brutal thrashing at Scrabble, when my opponent played the word 'SCOPIE' on a triple word score, I kind of played around with it for a few years and didn’t really learn much and wasn’t very good for the first two years, but then I started a band with my cousin and two mates from school
Connolly became a permanent member of the band near the end of 2002.
More recently Connolly played with Feeder live at the Isle Of Wight festival on Sunday 12 June 2016.
